# Pointo Expo prototype — environment variables
#
# Any variable prefixed with EXPO_PUBLIC_ is inlined by Metro at bundle
# time and is therefore safe to commit only when the value is *not*
# secret. Anything sensitive (private API keys, signing tokens) must
# live in EAS Secrets or a server-only environment instead.
#
# Copy this file to `.env` to enable the real OTP backend in local dev:
#
#   cp .env.example .env

# Phase 3.1 — Auth provider selection
# - leave both unset (or set EXPO_PUBLIC_AUTH_PROVIDER=mock) to use the
#   built-in MockAuthProvider with the universal `000000` demo code.
# - set EXPO_PUBLIC_AUTH_API_URL alone, or set
#   EXPO_PUBLIC_AUTH_PROVIDER=http, to use HttpAuthProvider against
#   any backend that implements the contract documented in
#   src/services/auth.ts.

# EXPO_PUBLIC_AUTH_PROVIDER=http
# EXPO_PUBLIC_AUTH_API_URL=https://auth.pointo.app

# Phase 3.2 — Server-side ledger sync
# - leave unset for local-only mode (transactions never leave the device).
# - set EXPO_PUBLIC_LEDGER_API_URL to enable HttpLedgerSync, which posts
#   every credit/debit to /v1/ledger/transactions and reconciles via
#   /v1/ledger/snapshot. See src/services/ledger.ts for the contract.

# EXPO_PUBLIC_LEDGER_API_URL=https://ledger.pointo.app
